Doctor Who - Real Time Webcast

[u][b]Synopsis[/b][/u]
There has been a series of mysterious vanishings on the desert planet Chronos in the 33rd century. Survey teams working for a university seem to have simply vanished amongst the pyramids on the planet. [u][b]Info[/b][/u]
Real Time is a webcast based on the long-running British science fiction television series Doctor Who which was then subsequently released as an audioplay on CD. It was produced by Big Finish Productions for BBCi, the interactive television service arm of the BBC and was originally webcast on the BBC Doctor Who website from August 2 to September 6, 2002.
